external_knowledge:
- 'Total score' is the sum of all scores recorded in the performance metrics for each session;
- 'Total time' is the sum of all time taken recorded in the performance metrics for each session;
- 'System notifications' are alerts or messages generated during the game session;
- 'Session ratings' include the counts of 'Excellent', 'Good', 'Average', and 'Poor' ratings given to the session.

- A user is considered an admin if their role is 'admin';
- The query focuses on users who have more than 5 game sessions;
- The average number of notifications and events per session is calculated for each user.

- "longer average sessions" refers to sessions that last longer than the average session length across all sessions;
- "better performance metrics" refers to performance metrics that are higher than the average performance metric across all metrics;
- "more than 10 distinct sessions" means there are more than 10 unique game sessions for that game version;
- "over 50 performance metrics" means there are more than 50 recorded performance metrics for that game version.

- 'Top performers' refers to sessions with the highest average `GameSpeed` metric values;
- 'GameSpeed' is a performance metric used to measure how fast the game runs;
- 'trigger_time' is the time at which an event is triggered in the game.

sql:
SELECT AVG(dynamic_count) AS average_dynamic_configurations
    FROM (
      SELECT session_id, COUNT(dynamic_id) AS dynamic_count
      FROM dynamic_configurations
      GROUP BY session_id
    );

